1 AN ACT relating to the use of algorithmic devices in setting the amount of rent to
2 be charged to a residential tenant.
3 WHEREAS, recent national data indicates that landlords of residential rental
4 housing use property management software to collude and raise residential rental housing
5 prices; and
6 WHEREAS, landlords engaging with the software supply real-time prices and
7 additional lease information to companies managing the software, who proceed to use
8 algorithms to fix rental prices; and
9 WHEREAS, the use of these algorithmic devices has been the subject of lawsuits
10 and poses a heightened risk of anticompetitive conduct, price fixing, and collusion, all of
11 which result in higher rents for residential tenants; and
12 WHEREAS, several municipalities around the country have prohibited the use of
13 algorithmic devices in setting rent;
14 NOW, THEREFORE,
15 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
16 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 383 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 (1) As used in this section, "algorithmic device":
19 (a) Means a device that uses one (1) or more algorithms to perform
20 calculations of data, including data concerning local or statewide rent
21 amounts being charged to tenants by landlords, for the purpose of advising
22 a landlord concerning the amount of rent that the landlord may consider
23 charging a tenant;
24 (b) Includes a product that incorporates an algorithmic device; and
25 (c) Does not include a product designed internally and used exclusively by a
26 landlord or a landlord's affiliates.
27 (2) A landlord shall not employ, use, or rely upon, or cause another person to
